An '''experience model''' is a description of a typical user’s [[perception]] or [[understanding]] of how a system works. 

==Models==
Experience models are visually represented by abstract [[diagram]]s or [[metaphor]]s drawn from familiar objects, behaviors or systems. [[User interface]]s implement a variety of experience models to enable users to quickly grasp what is happening in the system, where the user is, and what the user can do next.

A [[software]] experience model may represent the relationship of one [[Software application|application]] to another, an application in relationship to various [[navigation]] mechanisms and other system or application components.

