{{Infobox artwork | image_file=John Brack - The Bar.jpg | backcolor=#FBF5DF | painting_alignment=right | image_size=300px | title=The Bar | artist=[[John Brack]] | year=[[1954 in art|1954]] | medium=oil on canvas | height_metric=96.4 | width_metric=140.0 | height_imperial= | width_imperial= | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=[[Melbourne]] | museum=[[National Gallery of Victoria]] | url=http://www.ngv.vic.gov.au/col/work/85242 }} [[File:Edouard Manet, A Bar at the Folies-Bergère.jpg|thumb|''[[A Bar at the Folies-Bergère]] (1882) by [[Édouard Manet]].]] '''''The Bar''''' is a [[1954 in art|1954]] painting by Australian artist [[John Brack]]. The subject of the painting is a direct reference to [[Édouard Manet]]'s 1882 work ''[[A Bar at the Folies-Bergère]]''.<ref name="record">{{cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/arts/record-price-for-painting-bar-none/2006/04/11/1144521342067.html|title=Record price for painting, bar none|date=12 April 2006|work=The Sydney Morning Herald|publisher=Fairfax|accessdate=27 November 2009}}</ref> It depicts a [[barmaid]] working in an [[pubs in Australia|Australian pub]] at the time of the "[[six o'clock swill]]". As in Manet's work, the patrons of the bar are shown in a reflection behind the barmaid. The work is considered a companion piece to Brack's later work ''[[Collins St., 5 pm]]''.<ref name="abc">{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2009/03/19/2520543.htm|title=Gallery buys The Bar|date=19 March 2009|work=ABC News|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=27 November 2009}}</ref>
The painting was first sold to a Melbourne art collector for 90 [[guinea (coin)|guineas]] in 1954.<ref name="record" /> In 2006, the painting sold for $3.12m, a then record for an Australian work of art at auction.<ref name="record" /> The [[National Gallery of Victoria]] acquired the painting in 2009.<ref name="abc" />
The painting is part of the National Gallery of Victoria's Australian art collection and exhibited in the [[Ian Potter Centre]] in [[Federation Square]] in [[Melbourne]].<ref>National Gallery Victoria Acquisition [http://www.ngv.vic.gov.au/col/work/85242 2009]</ref>
